Attempt to help Votersdaily an attempt to scrape the contents of government schedules and combine that event data into a single datastore. 
Lang: PHP 5.2.x
Author: Chauncey Thorn chaunceyt@gmail.com

NOTE: Work in progress!
CHANGELOG

08-15-2009 
- initial import of HouseSchedule.php parser - http://www.house.gov/house/House_Calendar.shtml
- initial import of HouseRollCallVotes.php parser - http://clerk.house.gov/evs/2009/index.asp
- initial import of SenateRollCallVotes.php parser - http://www.senate.gov/legislative/LIS/roll_call_lists/vote_menu_111_1.xml
- modified code so all parser(s) are executed by ScraperScheduler (run.php)

08-16-2009
- initial import of SenateCalendar.php http://democrats.senate.gov/calendar/2009-08.html
- inital import of PresidentialActions.php http://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing_room/PresidentialActions/
- initial support for couchdb using: http://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/Getting_started_with_PHP
- initial import of SupremeCountCourtOrders.php http://www.supremecourtus.gov/orders/08ordersofthecourt.html
- support for couchdb and csv 
- initial import of http://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing_room/nominations_and_appointments/ 
    using the API http://www.socrata.com/views/n5m4-mism/rows.xml?accessType=API 
- changed VotersDaily to EventScraper
- support for cli argv couchdb or csv (default: couchdb)
- initial import of http://www.whitehouse.gov/weekly_address/ 
    using   

08-17-2009
- initial import of SenateLegislativeSchedule.php http://www.senate.gov/pagelayout/legislative/one_item_and_teasers/2009_schedule.htm
    buggy end_date - having to deal with May 25-29 and un 29-Jul 3 as start - end dates.
